 rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: underline;">B3-3.4-02</a>, AECOM / Jacobs / Stantec W-2 + RSU under B3-3.1-01 + B3-3.1-09, staff W-2 + bonus under B3-3.1-01, and solo Schedule C with Form 1084 cash-flow addbacks under B3-3.3-02, plus the substantial tax-advantaged differentiator that <strong>architecture and engineering services are EXPLICITLY EXCLUDED from SSTB classification under IRC Section 199A</strong> &mdash; meaning architect and engineer partners and solo practitioners receive favorable QBI deduction treatment without income-based phase-out (distinct from legal, accounting, and consulting which ARE on the SSTB list and face full phase-out at higher income).</p>
