onal reciprocity fees, Florida BOAF Board of Architecture and Interior Design and FBPE Board of Professional Engineers license fees, AIA NSPE ASCE ASME IEEE AIChE professional society dues, continuing education for license renewal, BIM software platforms (AutoCAD, Revit, ArchiCAD, SketchUp, Rhinoceros 3D, MicroStation, Civil 3D, Bentley products) at $2K-$10K annually, and specialty engineering analysis software (ETABS, SAP2000, ANSYS, COMSOL). Fannie Mae B3-3.1-01 variable income with 24-month average for staff PE/RA W-2 plus bonus and AECOM/Jacobs/Stantec W-2 base, B3-3.1-09 other sources for AECOM/Jacobs/Stantec/Tetra Tech/Parsons/WSP publicly listed firm RSU continuing vesting and Black &amp; Veatch / Burns &amp; McDonnell ESOP equity, B3-3.4-02 partnership and S-corporation analysis for PE/PA/PLLC firm principal K-1 with Form 1084 cash-flow addbacks at partnership level, B3-3.3-02 self-employed Schedule C analysis with Form 1084 cash-flow addbacks for solo AE practitioners. Conventional Conforming, Conventional Jumbo, Conventional Super-Jumbo, Multi-Source W-2 + RSU (publicly listed AE firm Managing Director), S-Corp Self-Employed boutique, Schedule C + Form 1084 solo, Bank Statement Non-QM, and SBA 7(a) AE practice acquisition loan program options. CRITICAL: Architecture and Engineering services are EXPLICITLY EXCLUDED from Specified Service Trade or Business (SSTB) classification under IRC Section 199A and Treasury Regulation 1.199A-5, meaning architect and engineer partners and solo practitioners receive favorable QBI deduction treatment WITHOUT income-based phase-out (distinct from legal services, accounting services, and consulting services which ARE SSTB with full phase-out). Florida hurricane code expertise and HVHZ (High-Velocity Hurricane Zone) compliance in Miami-Dade and Broward, marine and coastal engineering for sea-level-rise adaptation, high-rise structural design, BIM technology, sustainability and LEED design, and engineering talent shortage industry dynamics." canonical="https://stairwaymortgage.com/professional-services/architects-engineers/">
